%% SQL Access Provisioning Sequence
%% Enable external SQL access → pg_duckdb schema → PgBouncer → connection string

sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend as Frontend
    participant API as API (FastAPI)
    participant Provisioner as QueryEngineProvisioner
    participant QE as Query Engine (pg_duckdb :5433)
    participant MinIO as MinIO (S3)
    participant Client as External SQL Client

    User->>Frontend: Click "Enable SQL Access"
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/projects/{project_id}/sql-access

    API->>API: Generate pg_role, pg_schema, password
    API->>API: Store ExternalAccess record (hashed password)

    API->>Provisioner: Provision SQL access
    Provisioner->>QE: CREATE SCHEMA project_{id}
    Provisioner->>QE: CREATE ROLE project_{id}_role WITH LOGIN PASSWORD '...'
    Provisioner->>QE: GRANT USAGE ON SCHEMA to role

    loop For each dataset in project
        Provisioner->>Provisioner: Generate staging SQL (read_parquet with S3 paths)
        Provisioner->>QE: CREATE VIEW schema.dataset_name AS SELECT ... FROM read_parquet('s3://...')
        Provisioner->>QE: GRANT SELECT ON VIEW to role
    end

    API-->>Frontend: 201 {connection_string, schema, role}
    Frontend->>User: Display connection details

    note over Client: External client connects via PostgreSQL protocol
    Client->>QE: Connect as project_{id}_role
    Client->>QE: SELECT * FROM project_{id}.my_dataset
    QE->>MinIO: httpfs reads Parquet from S3
    MinIO-->>QE: Parquet data
    QE-->>Client: Query results

    note over API: Sync keeps views current with dataset changes
    User->>Frontend: Click "Sync"
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/projects/{project_id}/sql-access/sync
    API->>Provisioner: Drop and recreate views with latest transform SQL
    API-->>Frontend: 200 {synced_at}

    note over API: Credential regeneration has 60s cooldown
    User->>Frontend: Click "Regenerate Credentials"
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/projects/{project_id}/sql-access/credentials
    API->>QE: ALTER ROLE ... PASSWORD '...'
    API-->>Frontend: 200 {new_connection_string}
